title: Visualizations, Manual Rotation and Much More
body:
**NOT READY TO BE MERGED YET** (hence `[WIP]`)

(This is the same as #75, but now vis-a-vis `master` as discussed in #79.)

This PR will feature a bunch of visualizations and necessary groundwork for them.
- [x] Q array visualization (the ideal sorts) #14 
  - [x] separate function to calculate item standard deviation #66 
  - [x] spin out weighting procedure from `qzscores()` into seperate `qfwe()` function #129 
  - [x] pop.sd helper function #126 
- [x] correlation matrix plot #92 
- [x] Various nfactor criteria and plots
  - [x] #148 communalities plot
  - [x] #149 bartlett's test and residual correlation matrix plot
  - [x] #150 scree plot!
  - [x] #151 Brown#s magic number 7
  - [x] #152 Watts Stenner criterion
  - [x] #153 Kaiser-Guttman
- [x] factor space plots #94 (**2d**)
- [x] factor composition plot #98

title: [WIP] Q Method Array Visualization
body:
Ok, it's (almost) done: 
- array visualization (#14 )
- complete with qdc differences
- also with new object produced by `qzscores.R`: _population_ standard deviation for each item across the flagged q sorts for a given factor as per #66 
- extensive testing with all options, other datasets, etc.

This is how it looks like:

![rplot03](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5372770/6320023/d9f2f76c-bad3-11e4-8d43-73053844fd23.jpeg)

Documentation is done, and `R CMD Check` is mostly happy, except for this stuff:
- [ ] copy editing, finding typos etc.
- [ ] pesky `ggplot2` namespace issue -> http://stackoverflow.com/questions/28662289/pesky-ggplot2-namespace-conflict-when-using-ggplot2-in-package
- [ ] some more testing with other people's data 
- [ ] adjusting font size, object thickness legend etc. once I see results on a scaled, printed page through `knitr` or something
- [ ] put `item_sd` creation in its own function, not inside `qzscores` as per #66 
- [ ] make `array.viz.R` and the newly created item_sd function accept only objects of class `QmethodRes`

I've marked this [WIP] for **Work In Progress** until the above remaining issues are solved.
I've pointed this pull request to `dev`, as per #38, but please _don't merge_ this until you and `R CMD Check` think it's ready for CRAN.

Hope people like this visualization and find it useful.

title: import/export/make.cards functions (2nd attempt, with better docs)
body:
Here we go, finally :)
This update on my import/print functions includes:
- greatly expanded docs, and examples for every function as per #44 
  notice that this is a bit tricky for _import_ functions; in every example, I first have to set the _relative_ path to `/extdata/importexample` – that's a bit ugly looking in the example, but makes sure these examples always work.
- make all non-essential arguments default to sth / optional #45 
- include input validation as per #49 
  also notice the already existing tests for consistency in `import.q.sorts` etc; they are _not_ always at the beginning of the code, but later in the code when stuff has been batch read in.
- make anything multilingual strictly optional, both in functions and expected directories as per #46 
- the wiki now includes a comprehensive explanation as per #32 , is also referenced in docs
- have `make.cards` accept arbitrary font sizes for items, defaults to pt 12 as per #51 

I've also run `R CMD check` and tried a bunch of cases, so far with no errors.

@aiorazabala I hope this is now (closer to?) ready for prime time. 
Let me know what you think.

Ps.: If there are still problems, we should just leave this Pull Request open until I resolve them (the PR updates automatically).
Pps.: if accepted, all the above issues should be closed.
